From: pik1 smart-proxy follow-up
Date: 2026-05-09
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add Config::dispatch_raw hook

## Motivation

`serialmux-rs` smart host uses `anchor::Transport` as a virtual MCU. It needs
to intercept `identify` locally, but for all other commands it would prefer to
forward the original undecoded payload bytes to the real MCU unchanged.

Today `anchor::Transport` parses the VLQ command ID internally and only then
calls `Config::dispatch(cmd, frame, ...)`. That forces proxy implementations to
re-encode the command ID when forwarding. A raw hook lets downstream proxy code
inspect or forward a command before any partial decode happens.

## What changes

### `anchor/src/transport.rs`
- Add `Config::dispatch_raw(&mut &[u8], ...)` with a default implementation that
  preserves current behavior by decoding the command ID and calling
  `Config::dispatch`.
- Switch the internal frame parser to call `dispatch_raw`.

This is fully backward compatible: existing `Config` impls that only implement
`dispatch` continue to work unchanged.

## Impact on pik1/serialmux-rs

After applying this patch, `smart_host.rs` can forward non-`identify` commands
without rebuilding the leading VLQ command ID:

```rust
fn dispatch_raw<'c>(frame: &mut &[u8], ctx: &mut ProxyContext<'c>) -> Result<(), ReadError> {
    let mut probe = *frame;
    if u16::read(&mut probe)? == CMD_IDENTIFY {
        let cmd = u16::read(frame)?;
        return Self::dispatch(cmd, frame, ctx);
    }

    let _ = ctx.to_exporter.send(frame.to_vec());
    *frame = &[];
    Ok(())
}
```

---

diff --git a/anchor/src/transport.rs b/anchor/src/transport.rs
--- a/anchor/src/transport.rs
+++ b/anchor/src/transport.rs
@@ -89,11 +89,22 @@ pub trait Config {
 pub trait Config {
     type TransportOutput: TransportOutput;
     type Context<'c>: ShutdownState;
+
+    /// Handle one raw command payload from the front of `frame`.
+    ///
+    /// The default implementation preserves the current behavior by decoding
+    /// the leading VLQ command ID and then delegating to [`Self::dispatch`].
+    fn dispatch_raw<'c>(
+        frame: &mut &[u8],
+        context: &mut Self::Context<'c>,
+    ) -> Result<(), ReadError> {
+        let cmd = <u16 as Readable>::read(frame)?;
+        Self::dispatch(cmd, frame, context)
+    }
+
     fn dispatch<'c>(
         cmd: u16,
         frame: &mut &[u8],
         context: &mut Self::Context<'c>,
     ) -> Result<(), ReadError>;
 }
@@ -190,8 +201,7 @@ impl<C: Config> Transport<C> {
     ) -> Result<(), ReadError> {
         while !frame.is_empty() {
-            let cmd = <u16 as Readable>::read(&mut frame)?;
-            C::dispatch(cmd, &mut frame, context)?;
+            C::dispatch_raw(&mut frame, context)?;
         }
         Ok(())
     }
